# Cursor Rules for Scientific Document Writing

## Project Context
This workspace is focused on scientific document writing using Markdown as the content layer, with the primary goal of converting documents to DOCX format using Pandoc.

## Markdown to DOCX Conversion Guidelines

### Table Formatting
- Use HTML tables with CSS classes for layout instead of Markdown tables
- Use `no-border-table` class for borderless tables
- Apply `vertical-align: top` for proper cell alignment
- Example:
```markdown
<style>
.no-border-table {
    border: none;
    border-collapse: collapse;
}
.no-border-table td {
    border: none;
    padding: 8px;
    vertical-align: top;
}
</style>

<table class="no-border-table">
<tr>
<td>Content</td>
</tr>
</table>
```

### Page Breaks
- Use `<div style="page-break-before: always;"></div>` for page breaks
- Avoid `<div class="page-break"></div>` without CSS definition
- Alternative: Use `\newpage` for Pandoc-specific page breaks

### Line Breaks and Spacing
- Use `<br>` or `<br/>` for line breaks within HTML elements
- Avoid using Enter/Return for line breaks in `<td>` elements
- Use blank lines for paragraph spacing
- Use `<div style="height: 20px;"></div>` for precise spacing control

### Multi-column Layout
- Use CSS classes for two-column table layouts
- Apply `two-column` class to the table element
- Use `width: 50%` for each column in two-column tables
- Example with `two-column` class:
```markdown
<style>
.two-column td {
    width: 50%;
}
</style>

<table class="no-border-table two-column">
<tr>
<td>Column 1 content</td>
<td>Column 2 content</td>
</tr>
</table>
```
- Alternative: Use Flexbox with `display: flex; gap: 20px;`
- For single-cell two-column layout, wrap content in `<div>` elements

### CSS Best Practices
- Use CSS classes for reusable styles (preferred approach)
- Always include `<style>` block at the beginning of documents when using classes
- Use inline CSS only for one-off styling needs
- Test CSS compatibility with Pandoc conversion
- Common classes: `no-border-table`, `two-column`, `page-break`
- Apply multiple classes to table: `class="no-border-table two-column"`

### Document Structure
- Use standard Markdown headers (# ## ###)
- Apply consistent formatting for scientific documents
- Include proper metadata for document conversion
- Use semantic HTML elements when needed

### Pandoc Conversion Commands
```bash
# Convert to DOCX
pandoc input.md -o output.docx

# Convert to PDF
pandoc input.md -o output.pdf

# Convert with custom template
pandoc input.md --template=template.docx -o output.docx
```

## File Organization
- Keep Markdown files in `docs/` directory
- Store templates in `docs/template-*` files
- Maintain sample documents in `docs/sample/`
- Use descriptive filenames with Vietnamese characters when appropriate

## Writing Guidelines
- Write in Vietnamese for Vietnamese academic documents
- Follow academic writing standards
- Use proper citation formats
- Maintain consistent terminology throughout documents
- Include proper document metadata (title, author, date, etc.)

## Quality Assurance
- Always test Pandoc conversion before finalizing documents
- Verify table formatting in converted DOCX files
- Check page breaks and spacing in output documents
- Ensure proper font rendering and layout preservation
